@article{10.1145/3797552.3797794,
	abstract = {Generative artificial intelligence (GenAI) has been deeply integrated into all aspects of the higher education in China. Its extensive application reconstructs students’ learning experiences through personalized learning protocols and interactive inquiry, empowers teachers in lesson preparation, classroom interaction, and post-class assessment, and promotes intelligent campus administration, balanced resource allocation, and scientific decision-making. However, its application still faces three major challenges: technically AI hallucinations leading to content distortion, insufficient AI literacy among teachers and the degradation of thinking abilities caused by students’ over-reliance, as well as ethically academic misconduct and privacy leakage issues. To this end, we need to construct a tripartite collaborative pathway of improvement: at the technical level, enhancing reliability through fact-checking mechanisms and hierarchical filtering; in the model development, creating specialized large models for education to strengthen teaching scenario adaptability and core competency cultivation; in the institutional construction, it is necessary to improve application norms, dynamic supervision, and ethics education, collectively building a safe, efficient, and equitable AI education application ecosystem.},
