	abstract = {The current assessment system for teachers' digital literacy has limitations, such as static indicators and neglect of practical scenarios. In the research on constructing a teacher digital literacy assessment system in the context of educational digital transformation, a dynamic, multi-dimensional, and operable evaluation model for teacher digital literacy has been developed. By employing mixed research methods including the Delphi method, Analytic Hierarchy Process (AHP), and empirical validation, a three-dimensional framework of “Technology-Teaching-Ethics” is proposed. This framework integrates emerging technologies like generative AI, thereby verifying the scientific validity and feasibility of the assessment system.},
